This paper deals with social network analysis and the reconstruction of latent similarities from observed social networks. The paper specifically mentions the use of random graph models and algorithms for reconstruction, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also discusses the multiplex nature of social networks, which is a topic of interest in the sub-category of cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The use of metrics and algorithms for reconstruction also suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
